$ Excel Object Model: Range.ClearFormats

`rng.clearFormats` removes formatting in the given → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range], such as that which was applied with → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range#excel-range-numberFormat[`rng.numberFormat`].

sa:
  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/clear_[range's `clear*` methods].

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range#excel-range-clearContents[`range.clearContents`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home/Editing/Clear[Home -> Editing -> Clear] -> Clear Formats
